    "client_msg_id": "a873066a-d806-45a7-9c2d-9967e9fb276a",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I thought this is cool too, and then I saw this tweet. (linked from HN)\n<https://twitter.com/mitsuhiko/status/1410886329924194309>\nIt's probably based on GPT-3, which means this will provide a most \"popular\" snippet, not necessarily a \"correct\" snippet. It is actually discovered that some of its codes use a questionable design (e.g. using a float for currency). I guess this is still usable for a boilerplate generator, but we shouldn't expect that much smartness in it. (which is a hard thing to do, because we tend to overestimate the ability of a black box.)",
